WEBVTT



00:00:00.928 --> 00:00:08.800
Well hello friends and thank you for joining me in our daily reading from God's holy word today we're reading mark chapter 12.

00:00:08.640 --> 00:00:10.656
Verses one through twelve.

00:00:10.528 --> 00:00:16.640
Now, in this lesson, we hear Jesus tell a parable about how he will be treated by others and

00:00:16.704 --> 00:00:18.720
And we are invited to ask,

00:00:18.848 --> 00:00:20.960
How have we treated him?

00:00:21.888 --> 00:00:24.384
Before we read, let's pray.

00:00:24.480 --> 00:00:27.520
Our Father in heaven, help us to hear.

00:00:27.392 --> 00:00:28.736
Jesus.

00:00:28.832 --> 00:00:30.528
In his name I pray.

00:00:30.592 --> 00:00:31.808
Amen.

00:00:32.672 --> 00:00:38.144
Mark chapter 12, this is God's word, and he began to speak to them in parables,

00:00:38.432 --> 00:00:43.872
A man planted a vineyard and put a fence around it and dug a pit for the wine press.

00:00:43.680 --> 00:00:45.440
and built a tower.

00:00:45.248 --> 00:00:48.896
And leased it to tenants, and went into another country.

00:00:48.864 --> 00:00:55.456
When the season came, he sent a servant to the tenants to get from them some of the fruit,

00:00:55.296 --> 00:00:56.672
Of the vineyard.

00:00:56.576 --> 00:00:58.368
And they took him,

00:00:58.400 --> 00:00:59.872
And beat him.

00:00:59.808 --> 00:01:02.048
And sent him away empty-handed.

00:01:02.176 --> 00:01:09.472
Again, he sent to them another servant, and they struck him on the head and treated him shamefully.

00:01:09.888 --> 00:01:11.424
And he sent another.

00:01:11.520 --> 00:01:13.344
And him they killed.

00:01:13.120 --> 00:01:16.160
And so with many others, some they beat.

00:01:15.968 --> 00:01:17.632
And some they killed.

00:01:17.792 --> 00:01:21.760
He had still one other, a beloved son.

00:01:21.664 --> 00:01:24.576
Finally, he sent him to them, saying,

00:01:24.352 --> 00:01:26.944
They will respect my son.

00:01:27.232 --> 00:01:30.016
But those tenets said to one another,

00:01:29.888 --> 00:01:31.520
This is the air.

00:01:31.424 --> 00:01:32.448
Come,

00:01:32.224 --> 00:01:36.128
Let us kill him, and the inheritance will be ours.

00:01:36.192 --> 00:01:37.632
And they took him.

00:01:37.408 --> 00:01:38.912
And killed him.

00:01:38.720 --> 00:01:41.184
And threw him out of the vineyard.

00:01:41.536 --> 00:01:45.024
What will the owner of the vineyard do?

00:01:45.632 --> 00:01:47.296
He will come.

00:01:47.328 --> 00:01:49.920
And destroy the tenants.

00:01:49.760 --> 00:01:52.160
And give the vineyard to others.

00:01:52.320 --> 00:01:54.272
Have you not read this scripture?

00:01:54.304 --> 00:01:59.072
The stone that the builders rejected has become the cornerstone.

00:01:59.136 --> 00:02:04.320
This was the Lord's doing, and it is marvelous in our eyes.

00:02:04.800 --> 00:02:12.160
And they were seeking to arrest him, but feared the people, for they perceived that he had told the parable against them.

00:02:12.224 --> 00:02:13.824
So they left him.

00:02:13.600 --> 00:02:15.072
And went away.

00:02:15.936 --> 00:02:25.984
Hey man, this is God's Word. Who is Jesus talking to here? Well, at the end of chapter 11, the chief priests and the scribes and the

00:02:25.504 --> 00:02:28.128
And the elders had come to him.

00:02:28.032 --> 00:02:36.160
These leaders had asked by what authority he came riding into Jerusalem on the colt of a donkey, like a Davidic king.

00:02:36.064 --> 00:02:40.032
And by what authority he cleansed the temple of money-changers who had

00:02:39.776 --> 00:02:42.336
He said, made it a den of robbers.

00:02:42.400 --> 00:02:49.920
He had said to them, I won't tell you, unless you tell me first, if John the Baptist was from God or not. in other words,

00:02:49.696 --> 00:02:52.032
Do you believe John or not?

00:02:52.128 --> 00:03:00.480
Because John was from God and John knew who I am. But they refused to say, and so he said, I won't tell you.

00:03:00.416 --> 00:03:10.464
And yet then he tells them this parable. And the parable is so clearly about Jesus being the Son of God that it does answer, though indirectly, the question

00:03:09.984 --> 00:03:12.032
The question of his authority.

00:03:12.064 --> 00:03:14.272
But it is so clear to us

00:03:14.304 --> 00:03:19.488
Because we know the rest of the story, he is the son who is killed.

00:03:19.808 --> 00:03:21.952
Well, let's unpack the story a bit.

00:03:21.984 --> 00:03:23.872
And consider its teaching.

00:03:23.840 --> 00:03:24.928
First,

00:03:24.768 --> 00:03:28.832
Remember all the good which God did for the world.

00:03:28.640 --> 00:03:30.496
He planted a garden.

00:03:30.272 --> 00:03:31.968
The Garden of Eden,

00:03:31.680 --> 00:03:41.728
For his creatures to enjoy, and people to have dominion over, to cultivate and bring forth fruit, Adam and Eve ought to have said, Oh, wow, this.

00:03:41.248 --> 00:03:43.488
Oh, this is wonderful. Thank you. Thank you.

00:03:43.488 --> 00:03:48.288
But they tried to take over and manage it themselves, rejecting the owner.

00:03:48.576 --> 00:03:58.624
Now, even after that, God was merciful. He replanted a garden and put his people Israel there in homes they did not build with gardens they did not.

00:03:58.144 --> 00:04:08.192
Did not plant. Deuteronomy 8 says a land of brooks of water, of fountains and springs flowing out in the valleys and hills, a land of wheat and barn.

00:04:07.712 --> 00:04:17.760
And barley, of vines and fig trees and pomegranates, a land of olive trees and honey, a land in which you will eat bread without scarcity.

00:04:17.280 --> 00:04:26.880
Scarcity in which you will lack nothing. A land whose stones are iron and out of whose hills you can dig copper. And you shall eat nothing.

00:04:26.624 --> 00:04:28.448
And be full.

00:04:28.032 --> 00:04:32.032
And you shall bless the Lord your God for the good land of the land.

00:04:31.936 --> 00:04:33.440
He has given you.

00:04:34.176 --> 00:04:36.160
Well, as for Israel,

00:04:36.416 --> 00:04:38.432
So, too, for us.

00:04:38.624 --> 00:04:42.432
And especially in America, full of plenty.

00:04:42.720 --> 00:04:45.024
God is good

00:04:45.184 --> 00:04:50.272
And he has given us everything we have. There is nothing we have.

00:04:50.016 --> 00:04:53.312
That was not given to us by God.

00:04:53.344 --> 00:04:55.392
And not because we deserve it,

00:04:55.232 --> 00:04:56.448
we don't.

00:04:56.416 --> 00:05:03.328
But because he is kind and generous and open-handed and merciful,

00:05:04.448 --> 00:05:06.240
But what did Israel do?

00:05:06.080 --> 00:05:12.032
Their hearts were filled with pride, and they forgot the Lord who brought them out of slavery and into freedom.

00:05:11.872 --> 00:05:14.080
Out of poverty and into wealth.

00:05:13.920 --> 00:05:19.328
Out of parched lips and empty bellies into a land flowing with milk and honey.

00:05:19.008 --> 00:05:21.312
So they would not listen to him.

00:05:20.896 --> 00:05:26.880
He sent them servants, and they beat them, treated them shamefully, and killed them.

00:05:26.656 --> 00:05:31.520
They persecuted God's servants. They rejected God's prophets.

00:05:31.360 --> 00:05:33.888
Though he had been good to them.

00:05:35.808 --> 00:05:40.896
So here's the second lesson. Never be surprised when people who claim to be God's people,

00:05:40.800 --> 00:05:42.592
Persecute God's people.

00:05:42.752 --> 00:05:45.536
And there are many today, too many.

00:05:45.504 --> 00:05:47.424
Who in the name of Jesus,

00:05:47.232 --> 00:05:49.184
But full of themselves,

00:05:48.896 --> 00:05:53.184
Don't build his church, but tear it down from the inside.

00:05:53.312 --> 00:05:54.848
Why do they do that?

00:05:55.104 --> 00:06:05.152
Well, those tenants said to one another, "This is the heir. Come, let us kill him, and the inheritance will be ours. They want God's stuff, but they don't want

00:06:04.672 --> 00:06:08.160
If they don't want God, they want to enjoy the world he has made, the

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:09.568
But not the maker.

00:06:09.568 --> 00:06:12.192
They don't want to live as children in his home.

00:06:11.968 --> 00:06:14.400
But as the owner and parent,

00:06:14.624 --> 00:06:17.056
never be surprised.

00:06:16.832 --> 00:06:21.792
When it is church members and church leaders who turn against God,

00:06:21.600 --> 00:06:23.232
God's Word.

00:06:23.104 --> 00:06:24.928
and God's servants.

00:06:25.920 --> 00:06:27.104
Third lesson.

00:06:27.424 --> 00:06:30.208
Do you see what Jesus claims for himself?

00:06:30.112 --> 00:06:33.920
He's not one among many. He isn't one of the servants.

00:06:33.792 --> 00:06:35.264
But the sun,

00:06:35.136 --> 00:06:37.216
He holds a unique place

00:06:37.024 --> 00:06:44.928
In the kingdom, he is the heir of all things, if you want to share in his inheritance.

00:06:44.864 --> 00:06:46.304
You can.

00:06:46.432 --> 00:06:48.704
But not by taking it from him.

00:06:48.512 --> 00:06:51.264
But by his giving it to you,

00:06:51.104 --> 00:07:01.152
By adopting you into his family, making you a co-heir with Christ of all things. It's not that God is reluctant to share. It's that we must receive

00:07:00.672 --> 00:07:06.112
Receive it as his gift through faith in Jesus who unites us or which unites us forever.

00:07:05.920 --> 00:07:07.712
To the air of all things.

00:07:07.904 --> 00:07:11.968
"'Blessed are the meek,' Jesus said, "'for they shall inherit the earth.'"

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:16.640
We become heirs of the world, heirs of the cosmos, Romans, chapter four.

00:07:16.416 --> 00:07:20.192
Through faith in the sun, because he is the heir.

00:07:20.320 --> 00:07:21.760
And he shares.

00:07:22.528 --> 00:07:23.776
Forth lesson.

00:07:23.840 --> 00:07:27.616
What will God do to those who reject Jesus?

00:07:28.096 --> 00:07:31.392
Well, verse 9, what will the owner of the vineyard do?

00:07:31.424 --> 00:07:36.448
He will come and destroy the tenants and give the vineyard to others.

00:07:36.448 --> 00:07:39.456
until he took his vineyard away from those.

00:07:39.232 --> 00:07:42.784
Disrespectful mockers and persecutors.

00:07:42.976 --> 00:07:48.960
And gave his vineyard to others, even to gentiles and pagans to all who receive him.

00:07:48.736 --> 00:07:52.032
He gives the right to be called children of God.

00:07:51.968 --> 00:07:57.600
He makes us part of his spiritual house built on himself as the chief cornerstone.

00:07:57.664 --> 00:08:02.624
But if you trip over him, if you reject him, be warned.

00:08:02.464 --> 00:08:10.208
God will come and destroy you who say in your heart, yes, let's get rid of the air. Let's kill him. Let's crucify him.

00:08:10.976 --> 00:08:12.608
But there is hope for you.

00:08:12.832 --> 00:08:14.464
Son, too, says.

00:08:14.464 --> 00:08:17.888
Now, therefore, o kings, be wise.

00:08:17.760 --> 00:08:19.072
Be warned.

00:08:18.816 --> 00:08:20.704
O rulers of the earth,

00:08:20.608 --> 00:08:24.768
Serve the Lord with fear and rejoice with trembling.

00:08:24.512 --> 00:08:25.632
kiss

00:08:25.376 --> 00:08:26.752
The sun.

00:08:26.816 --> 00:08:28.608
Lest he be angry,

00:08:28.480 --> 00:08:30.496
And you perish in the way.

00:08:30.464 --> 00:08:33.184
For his wrath is quickly kindled.

00:08:33.376 --> 00:08:34.848
Blast,

00:08:35.136 --> 00:08:38.880
Are all who take refuge in him.

00:08:39.616 --> 00:08:41.312
May you do so.

00:08:42.112 --> 00:08:43.296
Let's pray.

00:08:44.736 --> 00:08:47.968
Father in heaven, your son is the heir.

00:08:47.904 --> 00:08:50.720
Have mercy on us in his name.

00:08:51.040 --> 00:08:56.032
And grant that we would be co-heirs with him of all things, for your glory,

00:08:56.256 --> 00:08:57.728
And for our good.

00:08:57.696 --> 00:08:59.872
In Jesus' name, amen.

00:09:00.896 --> 00:09:04.096
Well, thank you for listening in, and I hope you'll join me next time.
